description:
&lt;p&gt;The Catering Department are currently looking to recruit a part time catering assistant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working within the chill room and your duties will include interacting with patient’s staff and visitors, preparing the meal trollies for all wards and delivering additional meals to the wards in a professional and efficient manner whilst maintaining a high standard of hygiene and cleanliness throughout the restaurant, kitchens and servery. Previous catering experience is preferred but is not essential as full training will be given. The Trust is committed to developing and delivering excellent customer focused service by treating patients, their families, friends, carers and staff with professionalism respect and dignity at all times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shift available: Monday to Friday and will required to cover both shift patterns of 07:00-15:00 and 11:30 -19:30 dependent on service needs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDebby MunnJob titleCatering ManagerEmail addressdebby.munn@meht.nhs.ukTelephone number01245 515122&lt;/p&gt;
